---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Us | The Sellers Family" description="Learn about Daniel and Katie Sellers and why we're choosing open adoption.">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-warm-800 mb-8 text-center">
      About Us
    </h1>

    <!-- Our Story -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-16">
      <div class="aspect-[4/3] bg-warm-200 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-warm-400">
        <p class="text-sm">Photo of Daniel & Katie</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-warm-800 mb-4">Our story</h2>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          <!-- TODO: How did you meet? Your love story in a few sentences. -->
          [How we met and our story — to be filled in]
        </p>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed">
          <!-- TODO: What's your life together like now? -->
          [What our life together looks like now — to be filled in]
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Meet Daniel -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-16">
      <div class="md:order-2 aspect-[4/3] bg-warm-200 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-warm-400">
        <p class="text-sm">Photo of Daniel</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:order-1">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-warm-800 mb-4">Meet Daniel</h2>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Daniel is a builder. He leads software engineering teams for
          work, but at home that means there's always a project going
          — a treehouse taking shape in the backyard, a board game
          he's designing with the kids, or something around the house
          he's tinkering with. If the kids want to help, he hands them
          a tool and shows them how.
        </p>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          When he's not building something, he's moving. He races bikes
          with local cycling teams, runs the trails in the foothills
          near our house, and picks up the banjo or guitar most
          evenings. He studied history in college and loves a good book
          — our house is full of them.
        </p>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed">
          As a dad, Daniel is patient, curious, and always up for an
          adventure. He's the one who turns a Saturday morning into
          an unexpected road trip, who sits on the floor to play, and
          who answers every "why?" with a real answer. He wants the
          kids to be curious about the world, and he leads by example.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Meet Katie -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-16">
      <div class="aspect-[4/3] bg-warm-200 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-warm-400">
        <p class="text-sm">Photo of Katie</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-warm-800 mb-4">Meet Katie</h2>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Katie teaches music at a Montessori school and has spent
          years as an early childhood educator. She spends her days
          surrounded by little ones — singing, playing, and helping
          kids discover the world through music and hands-on learning.
          It's not just what she does; it's who she is.
        </p>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          She grew up in Santa Rosa, California making music with her
          dad — a folk and blues guitarist who spent his life
          performing. She grew up backstage, on stage, and in living
          rooms full of songs. She carried that love of music to Utah,
          where she wrote and performed her own folk songs. Now that
          music lives in our home. Katie plays for the kids, sings at
          bedtime, and there's almost always something playing in the
          kitchen while dinner comes together. A child in our family
          would grow up the same way Katie did — with music all around
          them.
        </p>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed">
          As a mom, Katie is warm, creative, and endlessly patient. She
          has a gift for meeting kids where they are — whether that's
          a toddler figuring out how the world works or a ten-year-old
          navigating friendships. Her years in Montessori have shaped
          how she parents: with curiosity, respect, and a deep belief
          that every child learns and grows in their own way.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Kids -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-16">
      <div class="md:order-2 aspect-[4/3] bg-warm-200 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-warm-400">
        <p class="text-sm">Photo of E</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:order-1">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-warm-800 mb-4">E — Big Sister, Age 10</h2>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed">
          <!-- TODO: E's personality, interests, what kind of sibling she'd be -->
          [About E — to be filled in]
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-16">
      <div class="aspect-[4/3] bg-warm-200 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-warm-400">
        <p class="text-sm">Photo of C</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-warm-800 mb-4">C — Little Brother, Age 6</h2>
        <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed">
          <!-- TODO: C's personality, interests, what kind of sibling he'd be -->
          [About C — to be filled in]
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Our People -->
    <div class="bg-warm-100 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-warm-800 mb-4 text-center">
        Our people
      </h2>
      <p class="text-warm-600 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
        A child joining our family gets grandparents, aunts, uncles,
        cousins, and a whole community ready to love them.
      </p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <!-- TODO: Add extended family photos with short captions -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="aspect-[4/3] bg-warm-200 flex items-center justify-center text-warm-400 text-sm">Photo</div>
          <p class="p-4 text-warm-700 text-sm">[Extended family — to be filled in]</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="aspect-[4/3] bg-warm-200 flex items-center justify-center text-warm-400 text-sm">Photo</div>
          <p class="p-4 text-warm-700 text-sm">[Extended family — to be filled in]</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="aspect-[4/3] bg-warm-200 flex items-center justify-center text-warm-400 text-sm">Photo</div>
          <p class="p-4 text-warm-700 text-sm">[Extended family — to be filled in]</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Why Adoption -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-warm-800 mb-4">Why adoption</h2>
      <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        <!-- TODO: Your honest "why" for choosing adoption -->
        [Your honest reason for choosing adoption — to be filled in]
      </p>
      <p class="text-warm-700 leading-relaxed">
        <!-- TODO: What does your family have to offer? What kind of life will this child have? -->
